The paper discusses semidefinite programming (SDP) bounds for error correcting codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of SDP is also related to optimization and algorithms (cs.DS), and the paper discusses the use of SDP in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of SDP in coding theory (cs.CC) and the application of these bounds to network coding (cs.SI).
